NEXT WEEK: ON ASSIGNMENT DISCOVERY
WORLD AT WAR THEME WEEK
http://school.discovery.com/ontv/themes/f2002_worldatwar.html
Witness powerful footage, eyewitness accounts, and behind-the-scenes=20
details from
the Pacific Theater in World War II, the attack at Pearl Harbor, and the=20
Korean and
Vietnam Wars. Discover the history of war-torn Afghanistan and delve into an
enduring anti-war novel.
Airs: Week of 1/13/2003 - 1/17/2003 on the Discovery Channel

World War II: The Pacific
Interviews with Japanese and American veterans and explosive combat footage
create an unsparing account of the complexities and brutalities of war.=20
Learn about
battles in the Pacific theater during World War II, from early warnings of=
=20
Japanese
aggression in the South Pacific to the U.S. dropping the atomic bomb on=20
Hiroshima
and Nagasaki.
Airs: Monday 1/13/03

Pearl Harbor
This stirring account of the Japanese attack on Pearl Harbor includes=20
never-before-seen color footage and interviews with military and civilian=20
survivors. Learn details of
the surprise attack and America=92s response=97its entry into World War II.=
=20
Hear the
story of a highly decorated, segregated Japanese-American battalion that=20
fought in
Europe.
Airs: Tuesday 1/14/03

Afghanistan: 12 Years of Violence
Chart the history of Afghanistan, from the Soviet invasion to civil war=20
between ethnic
tribes to the rise of the Taliban. This war-torn country was once home to=
 many
sophisticated, educated, and artistic people. But by the late 1990s, it=20
became an
international center for smuggling drugs and precious stones=97and the=20
headquarters
of Osama bin Laden.
Airs: Wednesday 1/15/03

Great Books: All Quiet on the Western Front
Erich Maria Remarque=92s novel, based on his own experiences, embodies the=
=20
optimism lost during World War I. Explore the changes experienced by the=20
main character Paul Baumer, an 18-year-old German soldier who plans to be a=
=20
combat hero. Examine why his story holds as an enduring anti-war novel.
Airs: Wednesday 1/15/03

The Korean War
It was the first full-scale exercise of President Truman=92s policy of=20
containment, yet it
became the forgotten war. Learn what set the stage for this conflict, why=20
Truman
and General MacArthur clashed, and how the shadow of Chairman Mao grew as
events progressed.
Airs: Thursday 1/16/03

The Vietnam War
Richard Milhous Nixon was the first commander in chief hired to stop a war=
 and
resolve America=92s divisive opinions about its soldiers fighting in=
 Vietnam.=20
Powerful
footage depicts a president struggling to bring an honorable conclusion to=
=20
a war
abroad, while scandal and subterfuge deal a dishonorable blow to his=20
presidency.
Airs: Friday 1/17/03

Assignment Discovery airs Monday - Friday on the Discovery Channel at 9-10=
=20
a.m. ET/PT; 8-9 a.m. CT; 10-11 a.m. MT. As a service of Discovery Channel=20
with Cable in the Classroom, each program is commercial free and can be=20
taped and used in the classroom for up to a year.

